manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: The Ideal Solution for Gaming PCs Named after the powerful shield of Greek gods, Aegis symbolizes strength and power. This new addition of DDR4 memory to the AEGIS family of gaming memory is designed for upgraded performance and high stability on the latest PC gaming systems. Give the quality performance boost your gaming rig deserves, no matter the game. Whether it’s FPS, RTS, MOBA, or MMORPG, let AEGIS Gaming DDR4 Memory be the strength of your gaming arsenal!

Designed for Gamers Available from a standard starting speed of DDR4-2133MHz, give the performance of your system a boost by increasing the amount of transfers per second over the previous generation of DDR3 memory. Upgrade your PC memory speed or capacity with the G.SKILL Aegis DDR4 series for a smoother gaming experience!

Built for Quality Built with the highest quality of hand-selected ICs and rigorously tested on major performance motherboard brands, the AEGIS Gaming DDR4 Memory is designed for the best compatibility and stability the widest selection of motherboards*. [*Please make sure to check the G.SKILL product webpage for the latest Qualified Vendors List (QVL).]

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best for price
reviews.reviewText: I originally got 2x of these (16gb) and recently got 2 more to upgrade to 32gb. They work pretty well and are super easy to overclock (3000mhz) using the XMP profile in BIOS. Probably the best RAM in this price range i highly reccomend getting this if youre on a budget and dont care about RGB RAM sticks. Make sure to clean slots/sticks and make sure they are properly installed or else you will have display and boot issues. This randomly happened to me while using it a few weeks after building my PC. And when I put in 2 more sticks. They are very sensitive to debris and how you place them but that goes for any RAM. BUY THESE over any other non-RGB RAM.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 31, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great affordable ram
reviews.reviewText: This is reliable ram. Purchased a 16gig kit back in 2018 for a build. 4 years later and the ram is still going strong. I just purchased another 16gig kit for a new build and threw my first set in for a total of 32gigs. They OC pretty well (3000) and the xmp profile worked immediately. Great value, reliability and quality.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 30, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Decent ram for a budget ryzen build. Easy to OC *updated*
reviews.reviewText: I bought this for a build I was doing for someone who's always bought pre fabs (Dell, hp etc) and they seem to die on them in a year or 2.So I said I'd build a system that will meet all your needs. I was given a budget of $1000 and I came in at $670. Using a 4 core ryzen and this cheap yet fast enough ram I was able to build a system that exceeded their needs.They are genuinely shocked how fast it is for how little was spent. So I'd you're doing a budget build this memory is great. I had no issues overclocking it either.*Update*They have had the system for a while now and I've managed to get even more performance out of this memory without increasing latency so it definitely gets my seal of approval. I also did some thermal testing and found it runs within spec even when voltage is increased.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 22, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works guud lol
reviews.reviewText: It works great I had one issue clocking it to 3000hz but then I realized I needed to up the dram voltage to 1.350 instead of the 1.200 that was stock in the bios it took me a little while to figure that out I ended up seeing it on the back of the package in summary don’t be dumb like me and clock it correctly I’m guessing most of the bad reviews saying it didn’t over clock was because of this
